.TH "LIGHTNING-CONFIG" 1 "June 2026" "lightning 3.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
lightning-config \- view and edit the effective lightningd configuration (FEAT-272)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B lightning config
[\fIsubcommand\fR] [\fIargs\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.nf
lightning config — a thin front end over the Core Lightning config
file (<dir>/config), modeled on `bitcoin config` (FEAT-271).

"Effective" = the conf value if present, otherwise lightningd's
compiled-in default parsed from `lightningd --help`. Writes route
through sudo + install -m 0640, preserving the conf's owner:group
(the daemon group model: in --system mode the file is owned by the
`lightning`/`_lightning` service account at 0640), so the operator
can read but a privileged step does the write.

The CLN config is flat key=value with `#` comments and key-only
boolean flags (no INI [sections]).

Subcommands:
  list                 keys explicitly set in the config file
  get <key>            effective value of a key (conf or default)
  set <key> <value>    set a key (sudo write; warns to restart)
  unset <key>          remove a key (revert to default)
  path                 print the config file path
  help <command>       detailed help for a command
.fi
.SH USAGE
.nf
usage: lightning config <command> [<args>]

   list                 keys explicitly set in the config file
   get <key>            effective value of a key (conf or default)
   set <key> <value>    set a key (sudo write; warns to restart)
   unset <key>          remove a key (revert to default)
   path                 print the config file path
.fi
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.nf
LIGHTNING_CONFIG_DIR   force the state dir holding `config` (tests)
LIGHTNING_DIR          user-mode state dir; default /var/lib/lightning
LIGHTNING_LIGHTNINGD   lightningd binary used for --help defaults
.fi
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR lightning (1),
.BR lightning-daemon (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Part of the \fBlightning\fR educational Lightning Network frontend.
